@startuml AI Trip Planner - Complete Sequence Flow

title AI Trip Planner - Detailed Execution Flow (Fast Mode)

actor User
participant "Browser\n(index.html)" as Browser
participant "app.js\n(Frontend Logic)" as AppJS
participant "api.js\n(API Client)" as ApiJS
participant "FastAPI\n(main.py)" as FastAPI
participant "trip_planner.py\n(Routes)" as Routes
participant "trip_service.py\n(Business Logic)" as TripService
participant "api_service.py\n(External APIs)" as APIService
participant "OpenStreetMap\nNominatim" as OSM
participant "Open-Meteo\nWeather API" as Weather
participant "Overpass API\n(POI)" as Overpass
participant "Groq API\n(LLM)" as Groq

== User Input Phase ==
User -> Browser: Fill trip form\n(destination, dates, budget, etc.)
User -> Browser: Click "Generate Itinerary"
Browser -> AppJS: submitEvent
activate AppJS

AppJS -> AppJS: handleFormSubmit(e)
AppJS -> AppJS: e.preventDefault()
AppJS -> AppJS: getFormData()
note right
  Collect:
  - destination
  - start_date
  - end_date
  - budget
  - travelers
  - interests[]
  - pace
end note

AppJS -> AppJS: validateFormData()
note right
  Validate:
  - Required fields
  - Date logic
  - Budget minimum
end note

== UI State Change ==
AppJS -> AppJS: showSection('loading')
AppJS -> Browser: Display loading screen
Browser -> User: Show loading animation\n+ progress bar
AppJS -> AppJS: animateLoadingSteps()

== API Request ==
AppJS -> ApiJS: apiClient.planTrip(formData)
activate ApiJS

ApiJS -> FastAPI: POST /api/plan-trip\n+ JSON body
note right
  Request Body:
  {
    "destination": "London",
    "start_date": "2026-02-21",
    "end_date": "2026-02-28",
    "budget": 2000,
    "travelers": 2,
    "interests": ["culture", "food"],
    "pace": "balanced"
  }
end note
activate FastAPI

== Backend Processing ==
FastAPI -> Routes: POST /api/plan-trip endpoint
activate Routes

Routes -> Routes: Validate CORS
Routes -> Routes: Parse request body
Routes -> Routes: Pydantic validation
Routes -> TripService: plan_trip(request: TripRequest)
activate TripService

TripService -> TripService: plan_trip_fast(request)
note right
  Fast Mode is the ONLY mode
  (no mode selection in request)
end note

== Step 1: Calculate Trip Metrics ==
TripService -> TripService: calculate_trip_duration()
note right: duration = 8 days
TripService -> TripService: calculate_daily_budget()
note right: daily_budget = $250/day
TripService -> TripService: get_date_range()
note right: ["2026-02-21", ..., "2026-02-28"]

== Step 2: Geocoding (No AI) ==
TripService -> APIService: get_coordinates("London")
activate APIService

APIService -> OSM: GET /search?q=London&format=json
activate OSM
OSM --> APIService: [{"lat": 51.5074, "lon": -0.1278, ...}]
deactivate OSM

APIService --> TripService: {lat: 51.5074, lon: -0.1278, display_name: "..."}
deactivate APIService

== Step 3: Weather Forecast (No AI) ==
TripService -> APIService: get_weather_forecast(lat, lon, dates)
activate APIService

APIService -> Weather: GET /v1/forecast?\nlat=51.5074&lon=-0.1278\n&start_date=2026-02-21\n&end_date=2026-02-28
activate Weather
Weather --> APIService: Daily forecast data\n(temp, precipitation, weathercode)
deactivate Weather

APIService --> TripService: {daily: {time: [...], temp_max: [...], ...}}
deactivate APIService

== Step 4: Points of Interest (No AI) ==
TripService -> APIService: get_points_of_interest(lat, lon, radius, interests)
activate APIService

APIService -> Overpass: POST /api/interpreter\n(Overpass QL query)
note right
  Query for:
  - Museums
  - Restaurants
  - Tourist attractions
  - Cultural sites
  Based on user interests
end note
activate Overpass
Overpass --> APIService: POI list with details\n(name, type, coordinates)
deactivate Overpass

APIService --> TripService: [{name: "...", type: "...", lat: ..., lon: ...}, ...]
deactivate APIService

== Step 5: Format Data for LLM ==
TripService -> TripService: _format_weather_summary(weather_data)
note right
  Convert raw weather data
  into readable summary:
  "Day 1: 12°C, Partly cloudy"
end note

TripService -> TripService: _format_pois_list(pois)
note right
  Convert POI array
  into formatted list:
  "1. British Museum (museum)"
  "2. Tower of London (castle)"
end note

== Step 6: Single LLM Call (ONLY AI Call) ==
TripService -> TripService: Initialize ChatGroq LLM
note right
  Configuration:
  - Model: llama-3.1-8b-instant
  - Temperature: 0.7
  - Response format: JSON mode
end note

TripService -> TripService: Build comprehensive prompt
note right
  Prompt includes:
  - Trip details (destination, dates, budget)
  - Calculated metrics (duration, daily_budget)
  - Weather forecast (formatted)
  - Available POIs (formatted)
  - User preferences (interests, pace)
  - JSON schema for response
end note

TripService -> Groq: POST /openai/v1/chat/completions
activate Groq
note right
  Model: llama-3.1-8b-instant
  Temperature: 0.7
  Response Format: JSON
  
  Prompt: ~3000 tokens
  
  Request: Create 8-day itinerary
  with morning/afternoon/evening
  activities, staying within budget
end note

Groq -> Groq: Process prompt\n(LLM inference)
Groq -> Groq: Generate structured itinerary
Groq -> Groq: Format as valid JSON

Groq --> TripService: JSON response
note left
  Response structure:
  {
    "destination_info": {...},
    "daily_itineraries": [
      {
        "day": 1,
        "activities": [
          {"time_of_day": "morning", ...}
        ]
      }
    ],
    "recommendations": {...}
  }
end note
deactivate Groq

== Step 7: Parse and Validate LLM Response ==
TripService -> TripService: Extract JSON from response
note right
  - Remove markdown code blocks
  - Clean trailing commas (regex)
  - Parse JSON
end note

alt JSON Parse Success
    TripService -> TripService: json.loads(response_text)
else JSON Parse Error
    TripService -> Groq: Self-healing request\n"Fix this invalid JSON"
    Groq --> TripService: Corrected JSON
    TripService -> TripService: json.loads(fixed_text)
end

== Step 8: Format Final Response ==
TripService -> TripService: _format_response()
note right
  Convert agent_response to
  TripResponse Pydantic model:
  
  - TripOverview
  - List[DayItinerary]
    - morning: Activity
    - afternoon: Activity
    - evening: Activity
  - SmartAdditions
end note

TripService -> TripService: Build TripOverview
TripService -> TripService: Build daily itineraries
TripService -> TripService: Calculate travel times
TripService -> TripService: Build SmartAdditions

TripService --> Routes: TripResponse (Pydantic model)
deactivate TripService

== API Response ==
Routes -> Routes: Serialize to JSON
Routes --> FastAPI: JSON response (200 OK)
deactivate Routes

FastAPI --> ApiJS: HTTP 200 OK + JSON body
deactivate FastAPI

note right
  Response size: ~15-30KB
  Total backend time: 5-10 seconds
  LLM calls: 1
end note

== Frontend Display ==
ApiJS --> AppJS: response object
deactivate ApiJS

AppJS -> AppJS: appState.currentTrip = response
AppJS -> AppJS: progressBar.style.width = '100%'
AppJS -> AppJS: displayResults(response)

AppJS -> AppJS: displayOverview()
note right
  Display:
  - Destination
  - Duration
  - Budget
  - Weather summary
  (NO EMOJIS)
end note

AppJS -> AppJS: displayItinerary()
note right
  For each day:
  - Day header
  - Morning activity
  - Afternoon activity
  - Evening activity
  - Daily cost
  (Professional card layout)
end note

AppJS -> AppJS: displaySmartAdditions()
note right
  Display:
  - Packing list
  - Weather tips
  - Alternate activities
  - Local tips
end note

AppJS -> AppJS: showSection('results')
AppJS -> Browser: Update DOM with results
deactivate AppJS

Browser -> User: Display complete itinerary

== Optional: PDF Download ==
User -> Browser: Click "Download PDF"
Browser -> AppJS: downloadButton.click
activate AppJS

AppJS -> AppJS: downloadItinerary()
AppJS -> AppJS: Initialize jsPDF
AppJS -> AppJS: Add title & overview
AppJS -> AppJS: Add daily itineraries\n(loop through days)
AppJS -> AppJS: Add recommendations
AppJS -> AppJS: Generate PDF file

AppJS -> Browser: Trigger download
Browser -> User: Save PDF file
deactivate AppJS

note over User, Groq
  **Performance Summary:**
  
  Total Time: 5-10 seconds
  API Calls: 4 (1 geocoding + 1 weather + 1 POI + 1 LLM)
  LLM Calls: 1 (vs 5-8 in agent mode)
  Cost per request: ~$0.001
  
  **Technology Stack:**
  - Frontend: Vanilla JS, jsPDF, CSS Variables
  - Backend: FastAPI (Python 3.11+)
  - AI: LangChain + Groq (llama-3.1-8b-instant)
  - APIs: OSM, Open-Meteo, Overpass
end note

@enduml
